21/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The mayors of Sofia, Skopje and Nis were scheduled to sign documents Sunday (21 September) launching the EuroBalkans Euroregion, which encompasses municipalities within the triangle formed by their three cities. 
The Euroregion will also boost co-operation in the Preshevo, Gnilan-Giljane and Kumanovo micro-regions. 
The protocol of intention for the establishment of the EuroBalkans was signed in October 2002 and is supported by the East West Institute and the Council of Europe. 
(BTA, SEE newsletter - 19/09/03)
